x\in\mathbb{R}^+
x + \frac{1}{4x} \geq 1
x+\frac1{4x}\ge2\sqrt{x\cdot\frac1{4x}}
f(x):=x+\frac1{4x}-1\implies f'(x)=1-\frac1{4x^2}=0\iff x=\pm\frac12
f''(x)=\frac1{2x^3}\implies f''\left(\frac12\right)>0\implies x=\frac12\;\;\text{gives us a minimum, so}
x+\frac1{4x}-1=f(x)\ge f\left(\frac12\right)=\frac12+\frac12-1=0
